                advance your career at liberty mutual - a fortune 100 company!
responsibilities:
collaborate with business partners to research and develop predictive analytic solutions that enable data-driven strategic decision-making
utilize data science techniques to manipulate large structured and unstructured data sets, identify patterns in raw data, and develop models to predict the likelihood of a future outcome and/or to optimize business solutions
mine large data sets using sophisticated analytical techniques to generate insights and inform business decisions
identify and test hypotheses, ensuring statistical significance, as part of building predictive models for business application
translate quantitative analyses and findings into accessible visuals for non-technical audiences, providing a clear view into interpreting the data
enable the business to make clear trade-offs between and among choices, with a reasonable view into likely outcomes
customize analytic solutions to specific client needs
responsible for smaller components of projects of moderate-to-high complexity
regularly engages with the data science community and participates in cross-functional working groups
qualifications:

the position requires a master’s degree, or foreign equivalent, in data science and engineering, computer science, or a related field plus three (3) years of experience in the job offered or a related field. also requires experience with each of the following: predictive analytic techniques and statistical diagnostics of models; predictive modeling toolset including experience with various machine learning techniques; sas, sql, teradata, r, and python; ms office suite; machine learning techniques including: clustering, decision trees, neural networks, random forest, boosting trees, support vector machines, nearest neighbor, and deep adversarial networks, and a demonstrable understanding of the advantages & drawbacks of said techniques; statistical concepts & techniques including statistical testing and its proper use, matched-pair analysis methodologies, glm/regressions, and properties of various distributions; modeling using unstructured data, including text mining, word vectorization, tf-idf, and bag of words; experience using web services including s3, aws, and azure; data visualization techniques including power bi and ggplot; distributed computing including hadoop, hive, spark, and mysql.

